   {:e #blake3 "d324a50547015c8ddcb7845649b6ef0102169f9802b699eb1b93f55e895e803f" :a :task/description :v "CONTEXT: Tests for CONCEPT-MULTI and FRONTIER-STEER — the two tasks that complete the gradient-descent-isomorphic learning architecture. UNIT TESTS (concept.rs): (1) test_assign_to_concepts_multi — observation matching 3 concepts returns Vec with 3 ConceptAssignment entries, sorted by similarity descending. (2) test_assign_to_concepts_single — observation matching 1 concept returns Vec with 1 entry (backward compat). (3) test_assign_to_concepts_none — observation matching 0 concepts returns empty Vec. (4) test_multi_membership_updates_all_centroids — after multi-assign, each matched concept's centroid shifts toward the observation. (5) test_co_occurrence_matrix_coupled — 5 observations each in concepts A and B, 3 shared → Jaccard = 3/7 ≈ 0.43. (6) test_co_occurrence_matrix_disjoint — 5 observations in A, 5 in B, 0 shared → Jaccard = 0. (7) test_co_occurrence_matrix_subset — all of A's members also in B → A nested in B. (8) test_frontier_explore — store with 5 :pkg/* entities, 2 explored, 3 unexplored. frontier_recommendation returns Explore for the unexplored entity with highest connectivity. (9) test_frontier_deepen — concept with variance > 0.5 and 3+ members. frontier returns Deepen. (10) test_frontier_bridge — two concepts with 0 Jaccard but connected via dependency graph. frontier returns Bridge. (11) test_frontier_empty_store — returns None (no bootstrap packages, no concepts). PROPTEST: (12) For any N observations (5..30) with random multi-membership (1-3 concepts each), sum of all concept member_counts >= N (multi-counting). (13) For any co-occurrence matrix, Jaccard values in [0.0, 1.0] and symmetric. E2E (scripts/e2e_frontier_steering.sh — NEW): (14) Fresh init on Go CLI with model2vec → braid model status shows model2vec. (15) 3 observations → frontier recommends explore (specific unexplored package). (16) 5 observations → at least 2 observations have multi-membership (appear in 2+ concepts). (17) 8 observations → braid status shows coupled pairs or bridge gaps. (18) 10 observations → frontier recommendation changes from explore to deepen or bridge (adapts to knowledge state). (19) braid status shows coverage N/M packages explored. (20) braid harvest → concepts with accurate multi-member counts. FAILURE DIAGNOSTICS: Log concept assignments (all, not just primary), cosine scores for each, frontier recommendation with score and rationale, co-occurrence matrix entries, coverage counts. DEPENDS-ON: CONCEPT-MULTI, FRONTIER-STEER. FILE: crates/braid-kernel/src/concept.rs, scripts/e2e_frontier_steering.sh" :op :assert}
